# Analytics consent and PostHog

## Initialisation order (critical)

- **`PostHogProvider` must call `initPostHog()` before `syncPosthogPrivacySignals()`** in the same `useEffect` (or otherwise guarantee `posthog.__loaded` is true before sync). Implement sync in **`lib/posthog-privacy-sync.ts`** so it can be reused.
- **Reason:** Parent effects run before child effects. Moving `initPostHog()` only into `PageViewTracker` (or any child) causes `syncPosthogPrivacySignals()` to no-op on first load because `__loaded` is still false — opt-in/opt-out from cookies and DNT stops applying until a `visibilitychange` event.
- **`PosthogRoutePrivacySync`** (inside the same `Suspense` as `PageViewTracker`) must call **`initPostHog()` + `syncPosthogPrivacySignals()`** on **`pathname` / `searchParams` changes** so query-only navigations (e.g. stripping `?ph_identify=1` after login) re-apply consent.
- **`PageViewTracker` may still call `initPostHog()`** before `$pageview`; `initPostHog` is idempotent.

## `useSyncExternalStore` and cookies

- **Do not use `useSyncExternalStore(() => () => {}, getSnapshot, …)` (noop subscribe)** for UI that reflects `document.cookie` or consent state. React will not be notified when cookies change after navigation on the same pathname (e.g. `/privacy` → `/privacy?analytics=opted_in`).
- **Use `subscribeDocumentConsentSignals` from `lib/analytics-consent-subscribe.ts`** (storage + visibility), and include **`useSearchParams()`** (with a **`Suspense` boundary**) when query changes matter without a pathname change.
- Applies to patterns like the footer opt-out note and privacy banner.

## Cookie vs browser signals (UI vs capture)

- **Green “opted out / cookie” UI** (privacy toggle section A, footer note) must follow **cookie-only** detection via `hasAnalyticsOptOutCookie()` and server `getServerCookieAnalyticsOptOut()` — not combined DNT/GPC, so copy stays truthful and CDN/header noise does not flip the card.
- **`PostHogProvider` / capture gating** may use **`hasBrowserAnalyticsOptOut()`** (cookie **or** DNT **or** `navigator.globalPrivacyControl`).

## Opt-out cookie names

- Prefer **`adp_analytics_opt_out`**; keep reading legacy **`ph_opt_out`** until fully migrated. Routes **`/privacy/opt-in`** and **`/privacy/opt-out`** must clear/set using the shared constants in `lib/analytics-opt-out-cookies.ts`.

## Verification

- After changing any of the files in this rule’s globs, run **`npm test`** — contract tests under `lib/__tests__/posthog-consent-contract.test.ts` guard init/sync order and forbidden noop-store patterns.
